parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Subframe and Engine Cradle Cross Member
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the subframe and engine cradle cross member can cause the axle shaft to break, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noise from the front of the vehicle
broken axle shaft
corrosion and rust on the subframe and engine cradle cross member
failure to pass state inspection due to rotted frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the K-frame can cause the vehicle to fail state inspection, making it unsafe to operate, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rotted K-frame
rusted wheels
failure to pass state inspection due to rotted frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the motorcycle to stall abruptly, especially when accelerating from a standstill, which can lead to accidents or serious injuries, particularly in heavy traffic or at intersections.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls suddenly when applying the throttle from a standstill
the motorcycle stalls repeatedly
the motorcycle stalls without warning
the motorcycle experiences sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the motorcycle to catch fire, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: Smoke coming from underneath the motorcycle
the motorcycle catches fire
the motorcycle experiences electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine oil leak can cause a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents, and can also lead to engine damage if left unchecked.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the engine
sudden appearance of oil droplets or puddles under the vehicle
oil smell or stain on the ground
engine noise or vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Check Engine Light and Gas Gauge
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty check engine light can fail to alert the driver to potential engine problems, leading to engine damage or failure, and a faulty gas gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Check engine light illuminates without a corresponding computer code
gas gauge reading is inaccurate or fluctuates erratically
engine performance issues.
